</p><p>Fraud and "fly by night" companies are commonplace in the entire housing industry. They go "bankrupt" (after big payouts to the owner) faster than restaurants, then the owner makes a new company, sells the "assets" and licensure to the new company, lather rinse repeat. The structure allows the fake "new" company to avoid having to fulfill its warranty obligations.
</p><p>It's a late-stage capitalism thing.</p></div>
