</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64195018"><p>Most of the residential rooftop solar businesses operated inefficiently with huge markups. It doesn't take much to upset that model. You can DIY a project for ~$1.5/W, $2/W if you have an electrician do the hookups. The solar installers charge $4/W. While 50% of the cost being labor is not unheard of, for an 8kW system it backs out to about $350/hour labor.  For comparison, a roofer gets paid about $20/hour.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64195018">
